Class GridNullOpt<T>

java.lang.Object
  org.gridgain.grid.lang.GridMetadataAwareAdapter
      org.gridgain.grid.lang.GridLambdaAdapter
          org.gridgain.grid.lang.GridAbsPredicate
              org.gridgain.grid.lang.GridNullOpt<T>
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, Cloneable, Iterable<T>, GridMetadataAware, GridPeerDeployAware, GridLambda, GridTypedProduct<T>
public class GridNullOpt<T>
extends GridAbsPredicate
implements GridTypedProduct<T>

This is a companion class to GridOpt allowing null values. Unlike GridOpt this class allows null for "some" values. This has less protection against referencing null reference but allows to distinguish between valid value (even if it is null) and "none" value.

Note that this class also implements Iterable interface so it can be used in monadic way with various method in GridFunc class. If this option's GridNullOpt.isNone() method returns true the iterator will be empty (which can be safely passed into any method that expects the iterable object). If this option's GridNullOpt.isSome() method returns true then iterator will have just one value (i.e. the value returned by GridNullOpt.get() method which can be null.
